==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wig-'', from Indo-European ''*weik-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''wig'', Old Saxon ''wig'', Old High German [[wic|wīc]], Old Norse [[víg]].  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[vincere]], Welsh [[gwychr]], Russian [[век]], Lithuanian [[veikti|veĩkti]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /wi:j/

===Noun===
'''wīġ''' ''n''
# [[war]], [[battle]]
#:''Oft ic wig seo, frecne feohtan'': often I see war, brave men fighting.  (''AS Riddles'')

